jk","Romaldkirk, Yorkshire, England":"Romaldkirk, North Yorkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1400–1441":"1400–1441","1405–1475":"1405–1475","1400–Female":"1400–Deceased","1430–1494":"1430–1494","1370–1440":"1370–1440","1400":"1400","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1494":"1494","about 1440":"about 1440","1370":"1370","1405":"1405","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Durham, Durham, England":"Durham, Durham, England, United Kingdom","Romaldkirk, Yorkshire, England":"Romaldkirk, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Matthew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the Christian evangelist, author of the first gospel in the New Testament. His name is a form of the Hebrew name <i>Mattathia</i>, meaning ‘gift of God’, which is fairly common in the Old Testament, being rendered in the Authorized Version in a number of different forms: <i>Mattan(i)ah</i>, <i>Mattatha(h)</i>, <i>Mattithiah</i>, <i>Mattathias</i>, and so on. In the Authorized Version, the evangelist is regularly referred to as <i>Matthew</i>, while the apostle chosen to replace Judas Iscariot is distinguished as   Matthias .  A related name from the same Hebrew roots, but reversed, is   Jonathan .  Throughout the English-speaking world <i>Matthew</i> has been particularly popular since the 1970s."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathew","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Matthew ."]}]},{"name":"Heslop","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Hislop  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Haslip","meanings":["English (London): variant of   Heslop  ."]},{"name":"Hyslop","meanings":["Scottish (southwestern): variant of   Heslop  ."]},{"name":"Hislop","meanings":["Scottish (Lowlands): habitational name from Hislop, on Hazelhope Burn (Roxburghshire), named with Old English <i>hæsel</i>, <i>hesel</i> ‘hazel tree’ + Old English <i>hop</i> ‘remote valley’."]},{"name":"Hazelip","meanings":["English: variant of   Heslop  ."]},{"name":"Heaslip","meanings":["Irish (Cavan): variant of   Heslop  . This is the usual form of the surname in Ireland."]},{"name":"Heslep","meanings":["English (North Yorkshire): variant of   Heslop  ."]},{"name":"Heslip","meanings":["English (Lancashire): variant of   Heslop  . In this form, the name is found mainly in Northern Ireland (Down)."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Matthew Heslop Lausoun was born in 1400, in Romaldkirk, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Hodgson Lausoun, was 31 and his mother, Ann Bainbridge, was 31. He had at least 1 son with Sarah Jane. He died in 1441, in Durham, Durham, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1400–1441":"1400–1441","1405–1475":"1405–1475","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1430–1494":"1430–1494","1370–1440":"1370–1440","1400":"1400","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1494":"1494","about 1440":"umbes 1440","1370":"1370","1405":"1405","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Durham, Durham, England":"Durham, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Romaldkirk, Yorkshire, England":"Romaldkirk, North Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1400–1441":"1400–1441","1405–1475":"1405–1475","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1430–1494":"1430–1494","1370–1440":"1370–1440","1400":"1400","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1494":"1494","about 1440":"noin 1440","1370":"1370","1405":"1405","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Durham, Durham, England":"Durham, Durham, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Romaldkirk, Yorkshire, England":"R